  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nutrition Emergency Response in Isiolo County</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As a result of the drought situation and migration in Kenya, there is need to target all the children in hot spots both within the static health facilities and the outreaches and hence the need to upscale the outreach sites. The action will entail supporting a one-off rapid mass MUAC screening across the health facilities. Following sensitization, Community Health Volunteers (CHVs) will be tasked to assess all the children below 5 years within their catchment population using the rapid MUAC tapes and refer them to the appropriate feeding and treatment program.   Additionally, the purchasing power amongst majority of households is challenged owing to lose of the main livelihoods; pastoralism to drought necessitating the need to cushion these households with conditional vouchers to support them purchase foods within the local markets to meet their daily needs.</narrative>
  </description>
